Raw dev notes -- RAG Pipelines: Cleaning Source Material for NotebookLM (Feb-March 2026)

Built two RAG pipelines (mikyab + rationalbelief) to prepare source materials for
Google NotebookLM. The main challenge: raw source files are messy and NotebookLM has
strict upload limits.

Pipeline stages:
- Standardize formats (PDF, DOCX, HTML -> Markdown)
- Assess RAG-readiness and overlap between sources
- LLM-based cleanup via Gemini API (async concurrent chunks)
- Quality gate to prevent hallucination/expansion (105% length limit)
- Batch into NotebookLM-sized uploads with H1 heading separators

Gemini cleanup pipeline learnings:
- ThinkingConfig + anti-hallucination prompt rules are essential
- Quality gate at 105% caught cases where Gemini was expanding/paraphrasing
- Split-retry for failed chunks worked better than increasing chunk size
- Had to block formula reconstruction -- Gemini kept "fixing" math notation
- Cross-file event loop bug: must reset SDK client between asyncio.run() calls

Also built a NotebookLM vs ChatGPT/Claude benchmark with Hebrew ground-truth questions.
NotebookLM's chunking internals are interesting -- documented findings.

Archived 75 one-off scripts during the reorganization. Felt good.

